<includeonly>{{#ask: [[-Has subobject::{{Category/ancestors|{{{category|}}}}}]] [[Category:Subobject field]] | mainlabel=- | ?For category= | format=plainlist | link=none | sep=, }}</includeonly><noinclude>
Returns the comma-separated list of subobject category names declared on
a category, including those inherited from ancestor categories.

Output format: `Category:Chapter,Category:Review`

This is a Tier A primitive — returns data, not markup. Each result is a
Category page that groups subobject instances of that type.

Parameter:
* category - The category name (without `Category:` prefix)

Example (iterate and render a section per subobject type):
 {{#arraymap:{{Category/effective-subobject-types|category=Book}}|,|@@sub@@|
   <h3>{{Category/label|category={{PAGENAME:@@sub@@}}}}</h3>
   {{Category/subobject-instances|subcat=@@sub@@|page={{FULLPAGENAME}}}}
 |\n}}
</noinclude>
